EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to education; requiring the board of trustees of
each school district and the governing body of each
charter school to develop a policy governing the provision
of certain services to pupils with autism spectrum
disorder; authorizing certain persons or governmental
entities to request the Superintendent of Public Instruction
to determine whether such policies comply with certain
laws and regulations; revising the definition of the term
“volunteer” as it relates to persons required to undergo
certain criminal background checks; and providing other
matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires public schools to provide programs and services for
2 pupils with disabilities. (NRS 388.419, 388.429) Section 1 of this bill requires the
3 board of trustees of each school district and the governing body of each charter
4 school to develop a policy governing the manner in which pupils with autism
5 spectrum disorders who have individualized education programs receive medically
6 necessary treatment or services from private instructional personnel in a school
7 setting. Section 1 additionally requires such a policy to: (1) require each school to
8 provide notice to the parent or legal guardian of such a pupil of certain rights; (2)
9 set forth protocols for private educational personnel to observe such pupils,
10 collaborate with educational personnel and provide medically necessary treatment
11 and other services; and (3) comply with the Individuals with Disabilities Education
12 Act. Furthermore, section 1: (1) prohibits a school district or charter school from
13 charging certain fees relating to the provision of certain services; (2) sets forth the
14 only requirements a school district or charter school is authorized to place on
-
