15 private instructional personnel; (3) requires the policy developed by each school
16 district and charter school to be made available on its Internet website and to a
17 parent or legal guardian who requests a copy; and (4) requires each school district
18 and charter school to compile a report containing certain information and submit
19 such a report to the Department of Education, which must submit the reports to
20 certain legislative bodies.
21 Existing law requires the Department to ensure compliance with the Individuals
22 with Disabilities Education Act, federal regulations adopted pursuant to the Act and
23 Nevada statutes and regulations governing the education of pupils with disabilities.
24 (20 U.S.C. §§ 1400 et seq.; 34 C.F.R. Part 300; NRS 388.417-388.5243) Existing
25 law further authorizes a person or governmental entity to request the
26 Superintendent of Public Instruction to determine whether a provider of special
27 education is in compliance with such laws. (NRS 388.4352) Sections 3 and 4 of
28 this bill make conforming changes to require the provisions of section 1 be
29 enforced in the same manner as other requirements governing pupils with
30 disabilities.
31 Existing law requires each volunteer at a public school, including a charter
32 school, who is likely to have unsupervised contact with pupils to submit his or her
33 fingerprints to the governing body of a charter school or the board of trustees of the
34 school district, as applicable, for the purposes of a criminal background check
35 before beginning his or her service as a volunteer and at least once every 5 years
36 thereafter. (NRS 388A.515, 391.104) Under existing law, a volunteer who meets
37 certain requirements is not required to undergo such an investigation. (NRS
38 388A.516, 391.105) Existing law defines the term “volunteer” to mean any person
39 who, without compensation, works at, assists with or oversees any activity or event
40 conducted or sponsored by the school during or outside of school hours. (NRS
41 388A.510, 391.1035) Sections 5 and 6 of this bill provide that the term “volunteer”
42 also includes private instructional personnel who provide services to a pupil with
43 autism spectrum disorder who has an individualized education program, thereby
44 requiring such a volunteer to undergo an investigation into his or her background
45 unless he or she obtains certain exemptions.
46 Section 2 of this bill makes a conforming change to apply the definitions in
47 existing law to section 1.
